    <a title="Anastasia Grindstaff" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/37231750-anastasia-grindstaff"><img alt="Anastasia Grindstaff" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1610502407p2/37231750.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2665382960?book_show_action=true">Jan 08, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anastasia Grindstaff" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anastasia Grindstaff" href="/user/show/37231750-anastasia-grindstaff">Anastasia Grindstaff</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780849947100" href="/book/show/10582688-when-god-whispers-your-name">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2665382960" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1163354957956788260">This was the first book I have read by Max Lucado and it was life changing! This book talks about various situations that every Christian has gone through at some point in their life. Through these life-changing situations Lucado explains how God is present even when we feel like he is absent. He provides excerpts of scripture in each chapter showing how God is always nearby not just for us but for all of mankind. The book ties in scripture, humor, and impeccable writing in each chapter. Each ch</span>
  <span id="freeText1163354957956788260" style="display:none">This was the first book I have read by Max Lucado and it was life changing! This book talks about various situations that every Christian has gone through at some point in their life. Through these life-changing situations Lucado explains how God is present even when we feel like he is absent. He provides excerpts of scripture in each chapter showing how God is always nearby not just for us but for all of mankind. The book ties in scripture, humor, and impeccable writing in each chapter. Each chapter has a theme and Lucado makes a masterpiece of each chapter by adding his unique touch to the chapter. Lastly, the book itself reads like a story. Each chapter is woven into the next and by the time you reach the end you see the big picture Lucado is painting. This book allowed me to get closer to God and gave me the ability to gain a new perspective on some very important things in my life. I highly recommend this as your next novel! <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="1163354957956788260" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


