  <span id="freeText15376134339986241075" style="display:none">I received this book some years ago as a birthday gift. I wanted to reconnect with my spirituality so decided to finally start reading it. Read it half through but could not finish it.<br /><br />It was very disappointing to see how consumerism affected even these types of books. Why? What’s wrong with us as a society? Why Lucando wants to make this book so sellable, that he decides to convert it into a novel or a movie script? But a low budget one, meaningless. I felt that I was “ingesting” empty calories when reading through. <br /><br />I now know that Virgin Mary had acne, and that I should be really kind with the ones that park my car or serve my food (is he really talking about tipping?!). Or that God decided to speak to a man from the red bucket that he was cleaning with one day; the first thing God said to him was to take off his shoes as he was stepping on a holy floor. <br /><br />Definitely a waste of time. <br /><br /><br /></span>
