  <span id="freeText2689473813284912166" style="display:none">Once again, if Max Lucado wrote it, you know it's going to be good. This is a collection of short chapters that talk about God and how he wants to have a relationship with you. Written in Max's personable style, some stories made me smile, some caused me to wipe away my tears, almost all resonated and made me think. Comforting, encouraging, supportive, hopeful, and inspirational. This book was passed along to me and I read one or two chapters a day. As with most of his books, this one had discussion questions at the back, so it would be good for a group to read together. I was sorry when I came to the end. An especially good book to read during this COVID-19 year.</span>
