<div id="review_3337582488" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3337582488" />
    <a title="Mason E Searle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32602965-mason-e-searle"><img alt="Mason E Searle" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1403860803p2/32602965.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3337582488?book_show_action=true">Jun 12, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mason E Searle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mason E Searle" href="/user/show/32602965-mason-e-searle">Mason E Searle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3337582488" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9533236555166907147">Not a bad little book. Max is simple, clear, and thought provoking. Good uses him as he always does - to point out obvious things we always glaze over. I recommend reading this as a daily devotional as each chapter is a small individual snippet of truth that needs to be chewed on and digested to be fully appreciated. A truly gifted author and worth the read!</span>

          </span>
        </div>


